last_episode_to_air.name: Meat Dog's Friends
last_episode_to_air.overview: Dog finds out meat comes from animals, and his friends are animals!

name: CatDog
overview: The life and times of a cat and a dog with a unique twist: they're connected, literally. They share one body with a Dog's head at one end and Cat's head on the other. Adding to their dilemma is Cat's annoyance with Dog, mainly caused by Dog's stupidity and Cat's up-tight personality. Characters: Cat - Cat is the smarter one of the two brothers, and is always hatching some kind of plot to get his brother to calm down, so that Cat doesn't get beat around and hurt. Even though most of these plots involve messing with Dog's feeble mind, they often backfire on Cat, much to his dismay. It may not show all the time but, he deeply loves, and cares for his brother Dog. Dog - Dog is the more lovable of the two brothers, Dog loves to play and party and play some more, he loves baseball and playing fetch with frisbees, balls, sticks, etc, He is very friendly, and happy, but does have a breaking point. He's very sensitive, and if he fails at something he feels horrible, and worthless

episodes.name: Dog Gone
episodes.overview: Cat decides he wants some quiet time to himself, so Dog puts on "the suit" and Cat finds out just how much he really misses Dog. He tries his hardest to read, write, or eat, but he feels so guilty that he makes Dog come out.

episodes.name: Fan Mail
episodes.overview: In a filler segment, since the pilot was too short, CatDog read their fan mail, but since Winslow claims there is no mail for them, Dog makes up a wild version of their origin story.

episodes.name: All You Can't Eat
episodes.overview: CatDog want to eat at a taco restaurant, but Rancid Rabbit bans them from entering. They try sneaking in numerous ways, but are caught every time. Eventually, Dunglap takes control of Taco Depot, and lets CatDog eat there whenever they want.

episodes.name: Flea or Die!
episodes.overview: CatDog get fleas, so they have to wear an unfashonable belt. Dog refuses to wear the belt. When he does, the fleas inhabbit Cat, so they fight over the belt. When the belt becomes useless, they find the fleas a new home.

episodes.name: CatDog Food
episodes.overview: CatDog become famious stars with ""CatDog Food"". But after the fame gos to Cat's head, he gets cocky, and insults Dog. He even gains a bunch of weight. It isn't until He makes fun of Rancid Rabbit, and ruins the deal that he relizes that he has made a change for the worst.

episodes.name: The Island
episodes.overview: CatDog try to go on a vacation, but they nd up in the middle of a giant traffic jam that never stops. After they make the best of it, they turn on each other when they need food.    Eventually, they make peace and try to get out. They end up on a bulletin board, and think they're on an island.

episodes.name: All You Need is Lube
episodes.overview: Cat saves Lube's life from a tick, so Lube promises to serve Cat always. But when he starts to keep Dog away, Cat realizes that he needs to rid himself of Lube. So, Cat and the Greasers make a plan where The Greasers pound Cat.

episodes.name: Shriek Loves Dog
episodes.overview: Cat tries to get Shriek and Dog married so the Greasers will stop pounding him. Then, he dreams about there life together, and sees how bad it would be.    When he wakes up, the beginning of his dream comes into play,    he makes Dog say bad things about her. The catch? Dog says that the insults were from Cat.

episodes.name: WorkForce
episodes.overview: CatDog work in Rancid's factory for ""Kravity Crunch"" cereal. Dog works harder than anyone else, and gets promoted to Prize-Stuffer. Cat, and the others at the factory are mistreated.    But when Dog is promoted to #1 prize stuffer, the workers revolt, and Cat and Dog reunuite just to become a prize.

episodes.name: Diamond Fever
episodes.overview: CatDog become greedy when the realize a Gopher has a lot of diamonds underground. Eventually, the rich makes them greedy, and forget that there brothers. At the end our hero's find out that the diamonds were really just rock candy.

episodes.name: The Pet
episodes.overview: The Pet-CatDog find a hurt Roach in the dump, and Dog wants to keep the Roach as a pet. Cat trys to get rid of until he's fed up with 'Roachy' the roach, and purchases a machine to annihilate it. When the Roach saves Cat's life, he realizes how wrong he was to stereo-type it.

episodes.name: Party Animal
episodes.overview: Cat invites people to his party, except for Winslow, that is, so Winslow throws his own party, which turns out to be more fun than Cat's party. So, Cat keps Mervus and Dunglap Tied up, and forces them to have fun. Then, when Dog joins the party, and Mrevis, with Dunglap escape, Cat enters the party, and everyone leaves.

episodes.name: Mush, Dog, Mush!
episodes.overview: Cat enters Dog in a sledding contest to win big money. He trains Dog in a winter version of their house. Whjen the race comes around, Dog races half way through it, and gets hypothermia. Cat feels bad and does the rest of the race himself, just for the Greasers to win.

episodes.name: Armed and Dangerous
episodes.overview: Cat is nervous because his Swedish Pen Pal Ingrid is in town.

episodes.name: Fistful of Mail!
episodes.overview: Dog meets up with a paperboy faster than him. This agravates him, and he trys everyday to get faster. When he realizes that he won't ever be, the former mailmen make a disgrase of him. Then...he relizes that the mailman is a person who has been faster since childhood, and he goes faster than him.

episodes.name: Pumped
episodes.overview: Cat is tired of the Greasers beating him up. So, when he sees an add in a magizine for drinks that will pumpyou up, he buys them. He dosn't like the taste, but Dog loves it.   So he gets Dog pumped up, and he relizes at the last minute that Dog has snapped. He tries to get more than revenge on the Greasers, and Cat tells him 'You're not really like this.

episodes.name: Dummy Dummy
episodes.overview: CatDog go to the store, and Dog buys ""Little Cat."" Dog pays more attention to Little Cat, and Cat trys not to mind. But when he relizes he is not wanted, he leaves, and trys to hitch hike a ride somewhere. Dog relizes how dumb Little Cat is, and makes up with Cat.

episodes.name: Squirrel Dog
episodes.overview: The Greasers plan another attack on Catdog, when Eddie the Squirrel messes them up. It turns out that Cliff has been glued to Eddie. He's then fired from the Greasers, and they go to CatDog for help. They graduate from CatDog's 'Freak' School. When Cliff realizes that Eddie's only on his Jacket, he beats up CatDog, and Eddie.

episodes.name: Brother's Day
episodes.overview: It is almost Brother's Day in Nearburg. Everyone is getting ready for it, except CatDog. Dog has gone out and bought a mud wrestling ting, and Cat... well he's just greedy. So when it comes down to it... Cat sells his lufa (a cats most prized possestion) to get money. Dog sells his Mud Wrestling stuff. They both bought eachother Wrestling masks, and the episode ends with the two of them attacking Winslow.

episodes.name: Escape From the Deep End
episodes.overview: Dog Breaks a rule of 'No Cannonballs' at the local pool. They are then forced to stay there as prisoners. Dog keeps breaking the rules, so he gets putin the 'Hot-Box.'   At this point, Dog obbays the rules, and Cat trys to bust out. Cat convinces Dog that Rancid is crazy, and they break out.

episodes.name: The Collector
episodes.overview: Cat collects every ""Mean Bob"" toy even if it means selling everything they own, while Dog plays with his one Mean Bob.

episodes.name: Full Moon Fever
episodes.overview: It's the Full-Moon, again, bringing out Dog's wolf-like instincts.

episodes.name: War of the CatDog
episodes.overview: It's CatDog's family reunion, and they fight over a trophy.

episodes.name: CatDog's End
episodes.overview: Cat wants to be alone, and wants a new butt instead of having Dog attached on him.

episodes.name: Siege On Fort CatDog
episodes.overview: CatDog are fed up with getting hurt by the Greasers, so they try to find out how to fight back.

episodes.name: Safety Dog
episodes.overview: Cat tells Dog to become more Saftey Concious, because Dog only has one life, while Cat his nine, so Dog becomes very safe.Almost too safe, so Dog does not want to leave anywhere, and that prevents Cat from leaving too.

episodes.name: Dog Come Home!
episodes.overview: Dog moves out after a bet with Cat, saying that Dog cannot last a day alone without him.

episodes.name: Nightmare
episodes.overview: CatDog and Winslow watch a horrow movie with ""Toothpick Head"", and become scared Tootpick Head is in their house.

episodes.name: CatDogPig
episodes.overview: Winslow tries to have CatDog have one more side to vote on what they should do for fun, etc., so a pig, horse, bird, and other animals live on CatDog.

episodes.name: New Neighbors
episodes.overview: Dog is frightened after reading a comic book about aliens invading, and he thinks the new next door neighboors, which turn out to be ""Grannies"", are aliens.

episodes.name: Dead Weight
episodes.overview: Cat tries to impress two ladies on a TV show, ""Really Incredible People"".

episodes.name: Neferkitty
episodes.overview: Cat reads a story to Dog about how Egyptians worshiped Cats.

episodes.name: Curiosity Almost Killed The Cat
episodes.overview: Cat reads Dog's journal, and Winslow catches a snapshot of him doing so.

episodes.name: Home is Where the Dirt is
episodes.overview: Dog gets angry with the Gorhper when he thinks his is meddling in his Bone Cellar.

episodes.name: New Leash on Life
episodes.overview: Cat tells a lie to Dog saying that there is a law where all Dogs have to wear leashes.

episodes.name: Just Say CatDog Sent Ya
episodes.overview: All of Nearburg's Dogs love ""Farburg Burger Bones"", but they get banned from Nearburg because Fargburg makes all of the money, so Cat gets  a plan to sell bones for over 5x the price to become rich.

episodes.name: Dog's Strange Condition
episodes.overview: Dog gets trees growing on top of his head after eating Pecan Pie.

episodes.name: Smarter than the Average Dog
episodes.overview: Cat is tired of Dog being so un-intelligent, so he makes Dog study & watch video tapes, so Dog sucks all of Cats smartness out of him, and in return Cat gets Dog's stupidity.

episodes.name: CatDog Doesn't Live Here Anymore
episodes.overview: Winslow missed CatDog after he thinks they moved away, except they are really on vacation.

episodes.name: All About Cat
episodes.overview: Cat tried to be the part of Abraham Lincoln in a play, but Dog gets accepted for the part.

episodes.name: Trespassing
episodes.overview: Dog smells his favorite fire hydrant and notices another Dog has been there, so he waits for the trespasser to come to the fire hydrant.

episodes.name: Send in the CatDog
episodes.overview: Dog had a surprise for Cat, and that was to join a Clown School.

episodes.name: Fishing For Trouble
episodes.overview: Cat's hairball wins them a prize at the amusement park, and Dog chooses a fish as a prize.

episodes.name: Fetch
episodes.overview: Cat wins a prize and has five minutes to call in and claim his prize, but Winslow throws a ball causing Dog to chase it all over town, while Cat tries to hang on to a phone.

episodes.name: The Lady is a Shriek
episodes.overview: Everyone in Nearburg is shocked to hear that Shreik is a girl, even the trees!

episodes.name: Dog the Mighty
episodes.overview: Dog gets a medal from Rancid Rabbit causing Dog to think he is a Superhero.

episodes.name: Hail the Great Meow Woof
episodes.overview: CatDog accidentally flies away on a kite and crashes into a statue of Rancid Rabbit, and the natives think CatDog is a God.

episodes.name: Battle of the Bands
episodes.overview: CatDog enter a band contest, but their competition includes The Greasers, who, from reading a ripped-up flyer, think it's just a huge battle.

episodes.name: Adventures in Greaser Sitting
episodes.overview: Cliff's Neice comes to town for a visit, but Cliff needs a replacement babysitter (Lube was supposed to, but he was unable), so Cliff makes CatDog do it.

episodes.name: The Cat Club
episodes.overview: Cat wants to join a Cat Club, so he makes Dog wear a cat suit.

episodes.name: Cat Diggety Dog
episodes.overview: This is a CatDog short where they go onto a stage and sing about how they get along.

episodes.name: Climb Every CatDog
episodes.overview: Cat tries to beat an old school enemy at climbing a mountain.

episodes.name: Canine Mutiny
episodes.overview: CatDog and their friends end up in a garbage truck and fall into water where Cat acts like a pirate.

episodes.name: Fred the Flying Fish
episodes.overview: Cat tries to disprove a myth about a flying fish.

episodes.name: CatDog Divided
episodes.overview: CatDog end up getting sawed in half in a magic show by "The Amazing Ray," but when they try to find the magician who did it, they find out he is a fraud and is in jail. So, they go to another magic show to put them back together.

episodes.name: The Unnatural
episodes.overview: Cat is very bad at Baseball, so he puts on a Dog mask making the Greasers think Dog is bad, and Cat is good.While Dog is not knowing.

episodes.name: Dog Ate it
episodes.overview: Cat tries to get Dog to lose weight.

episodes.name: Dopes on Slopes
episodes.overview: Cat tries to teach Dog how to ski, but when Dog jumps off the ski lift, a crazy series of events happen.

episodes.name: Spaced Out
episodes.overview: Everybody in Nearburg is antispating the new Mean Bob movie coming out, except for Cat, that is.

episodes.name: Nine Lives
episodes.overview: While doing some cleaning in the attic, Dog releases Cat's other eight lives, which run around causing havoc in town, so CatDog have to catch them all.

episodes.name: Dem Bones
episodes.overview: While at a museum, Dog wants to eat the bones of a dinosaur.

episodes.name: Winslow's Home Videos
episodes.overview: Winslow shows embarrassing home videos of CatDog.

episodes.name: You're Fired
episodes.overview: Taululah wants a soulmate, and it turns out that CatDog is a great match for her.

episodes.name: Showdown at Hole 18
episodes.overview: Cat is trying to win the trophy for goldf that Rancid Rabbit owns, so Rancid tries to do anything in his power to make CatDog lose.

episodes.name: Sneezie Dog
episodes.overview: CatDog are convinced that Dog is allergic to Cat. Trying to make Dog stop sneezing, he risks shaving himself. But that doesn't even work.

episodes.name: It's a Wonderful Half Life
episodes.overview: Cat & Dog dream about being seperated in their dreams and realize they are lucky to have each other.

episodes.name: Shepherd Dog
episodes.overview: Dog becomes a Sheperd Dog for a lady.

episodes.name: Surfin' CatDog
episodes.overview: Cat is trying to impress girl, even if it means surfing against the Greasers in a contest.

episodes.name: Guess Who's Going to be Dinner!
episodes.overview: Cat wants to eat Winslow after remembering that it is strange for a cat not to be eating mice.

episodes.name: Dog Power
episodes.overview: Cat is late paying the electric bill, so he tries other ways to save electricity.

episodes.name: It's a Jungle in Here!
episodes.overview: Sally, Cat's crush from second grade is coming for a visit, so Cat wants the house spotless and clean, but it turns into a jungle, literally.

episodes.name: The House of CatDog
episodes.overview: Rancid Rabbit wants to tear down CatDog's house for a freeway.

episodes.name: CatDog Campers
episodes.overview: Cat and Dog are campers in this episode, and they fight while camping, and end up in a dangerous situation.

episodes.name: Let the Games Begin!
episodes.overview: CatDog gets thrown in jail with the Greasers.

episodes.name: Winslow Falls in Love
episodes.overview: CatDog are tired of Winslow picking on them, so they try to find Winslow a soulmate.

episodes.name: Sumo Enchanted Evening
episodes.overview: CatDog eat a lot of food in Rancid Rabbit's new restaurant, and the bill turns out to be $34,000.00. CatDog end up gaining a lot of weight, so they challenge Rancid Rabbit to a sumo fight.

episodes.name: Hotel CatDog
episodes.overview: Cat tries to make some money by turning their house into a hotel. It all goes wrong when completely different people are right next to each other, driving the guests mad, which drives CatDog crazy.

episodes.name: Rodeo CatDog
episodes.overview: CatDog go into a rodeo show, and end up being famous cowboys! But first, will they survive the killer bull?

episodes.name: Teeth For Two
episodes.overview: CatDog go into the dentist office for a checkup, and his teeth end up being bad after Dog eating garbage, so Cat and Dog try to ruin each other's teeth by shoving teeth-rotting food down their throat.

episodes.name: Sweet and Lola
episodes.overview: There is a new bird in town, and her name is Lola. She moves in to the tree next to CatDog's house, because she wants to study them. CatDog get tired of her invading their privacy, so they try to get her to leave.

episodes.name: Rich Shriek, Poor Shriek
episodes.overview: Everyone finds out that Shriek is rich.

episodes.name: CatDogula
episodes.overview: CatDog celebrate Halloween, with Cat dressed as a famous surfer and Dog dressed as a vampire named "CatDogula", little does CatDog know that Nearberg is in great danger by bloodsucking vampire ticks. Now with Dog a vampire, and himself not, Cat has to dump a massive amount of Garlic juice onto Dog by midnight, or the whole town might turn into vampires.

episodes.name: Remain Seated
episodes.overview: Cat is bored and wants some fun, so CatDog go to the amusement park Mervis and Dunglap work at. Dog is eager to try the biggest and scariest roller coaster, which Cat is too scared to ride.

episodes.name: CatDog Catcher
episodes.overview: Rancid is talking a gold bath and the gold stops coming out, so he tries to make more money by making Dogs have licenses to not go to jail.

episodes.name: Talking Turkey
episodes.overview: Dog tries to save a turkey named Walt from being eaten by Cat and Rancid, but Cat soon takes Dog's side and helps keep their guests' minds on something other than turkey.

episodes.name: A Very CatDog Christmas
episodes.overview: Cat sells himself (and Dog) to Rancid's bratty preschooler niece Rancine as a Christmas gift, but Santa Claus gets angry when he finds out and cancels Christmas. The people of Nearburg are maddened by this, and a hunt for the brothers begins.

episodes.name: Shriek on Ice
episodes.overview: While Cliff and Lube are getting pleasure out of beating up CatDog, Shriek decides that there is more to life and decides to pursue her dream to be an ice skater.

episodes.name: No Thanks for the Memories
episodes.overview: Dog gets a touch of amnesia after getting hit with an appliance that falls on his head, in which starts up a whole chain of people causing Dog to get amnesia, telling him things about himself that aren't true.

episodes.name: Extra! Extra!
episodes.overview: CatDog become paperboys because all of the others quit when Dog chases them.

episodes.name: CatDog Squared
episodes.overview: CatDog finds another CatDog, DanStan, or so they think, because they other CatDogs are really frauds and want to sleep in CatDog's house and steal CatDog's trophy.

episodes.name: CatDog 3001
episodes.overview: Cat goes too far in teasing Winslow, and CatDog ends up in the year 3001.

episodes.name: Cloud Bursting
episodes.overview: Cat ruins Lola's prize winning machine, and gets in trouble after doing so.

episodes.name: Royal Dog
episodes.overview: CatDog see a picture in a museum that has a striking resemblance to them, and CatDog end up in England reliving the story behind it.

episodes.name: Springtime For CatDog
episodes.overview: Lorraine falls in love with both Cat and Dog, so she has to choose which one she wants.

episodes.name: A Dog Ate My Homework
episodes.overview: Cat comes up with a money-making scheme where a Dog eats people's homework.

episodes.name: The End
episodes.overview: Nearburg fears it is the end of the world after seeing a cloud shaped like an evil skull.

episodes.name: Cliff's Little Secret
episodes.overview: CatDog realizes that Cliff is taking Ballet lessons, and are no longer scared of him.

episodes.name: Freak Show
episodes.overview: CatDog joins a freak show to earn some cash.

episodes.name: Fire Dog
episodes.overview: CatDog becomes a fire dog at the fire department.

episodes.name: Dog Show
episodes.overview: Dog enters a Dog show and Cat dresses up as a Dog tail.

episodes.name: The Geekers
episodes.overview: The Greasers make fun of CatDog and their friends and call them the 'Geekers.' CatDog and his friends decide to make their own club: "The Geeker".

episodes.name: The Golden Hydrant
episodes.overview: CatDog find what they think is the 'Golden Hydrant'. They put the Golden Hydrant up for viewing in their own museum. They charge money for people to go see it.

episodes.name: Lube in Love
episodes.overview: Lube is seeking work at a gas station and falls in love with a girl there.

episodes.name: Picture This
episodes.overview: Dog becomes obsessed with photography, and takes pictures of a lot of people, even embarrassing ones.

episodes.name: Stunt CatDog
episodes.overview: CatDog become stuntmen in a Rancid Rabbit film, but Cat is only in it to kiss Taululah.

episodes.name: Greasers in the Mist
episodes.overview: CatDog tries to find out the "pork fat" to defeat the Greasers, and Lola helps them.

episodes.name: Doo Wop Diggety
episodes.overview: Winslow makes CatDog and the Greasers a successful band.

episodes.name: CatDogumentary
episodes.overview: Lola is hired to make a documentary on CatDog and if she screws up, she is in trouble!

episodes.name: Kooky Prank Day
episodes.overview: It's the yearly Kooky Prank Day that Cat hates because everyone pulls a prank on him, but this year he has a plan. He will use a fake flying saucer to convince everyone that aliens are attacking.

episodes.name: Back To School
episodes.overview: Cat missed his last day of school, so he didn't graduate, so he goes back to school to get his Diploma.

episodes.name: Monster Truck Folly
episodes.overview: Dog gets Cat obsessed with Monster Truck shows, and Cat becomes crazy!

episodes.name: CatDog's Gold
episodes.overview: Cat wants to sell bee's honey for money, but Dog just wants to eat all of it.

episodes.name: Silents Please!
episodes.overview: Randolph announces that ear infections, etc. would begin in Nearburg, and when it happens the episode turns black and white and has no sound.

episodes.name: Gorilla My Dreams
episodes.overview: A gorilla ends up on CatDog's doorstep, and Cat realises that the Gorilla would be a great addiion to their bowling team.

episodes.name: Seeing Eye Dog
episodes.overview: A rich blind fellow, Mr. Wolfington needs to hire a new seeing eye dog, so he agrees to hire Dog from CatDog. Cat is overjoyed because he finally is living in the lap of luxury as he always dreamed. CatDog overindulge and eat the finest foods, but something that they eat is just a little too rich for Dog, that he suffers a severe allergic reaction and can't see the next day when Mr. Wolfington needs him the most, to meet his friend in France.

episodes.name: Rinky Dinks
episodes.overview: Winterwonderland has hit Nearburg, and lots of folks want to enjoy Lake Nearburg and ice skate. The Greasers were there first playing hockey, and threaten CatDog and thier buddy's to move it or else.

episodes.name: Hypno-Teased
episodes.overview: Dog orders a hypnotism kit, and inside is a book and a Monkey's paw. Cat at first is skeptical until Dog successfully hypnotizes Winslow. Convinced that it works, Winslow cleverly convinces Cat that he can be invincable, like the greatest dancer or a fierce fighter, even to defeat the Greasers.

episodes.name: CatDog Candy
episodes.overview: The inseparable duo concoct a tasty confection, but with an unforeseen side effect.

episodes.name: Movin' On Up
episodes.overview: CatDog moves into an area where their Uncle Horseduck died, and it was in their will to let CatDog live there, but Rancid Rabbit is ther neighbor and will do anything to keep them staying.

episodes.name: New Cat in Town
episodes.overview: Eddie the Squirell is tired of the Greaser Dogs "pounding" him, so he invents a huge Cat to get back at the Greasers.

episodes.name: CatDog's Booty
episodes.overview: CatDog tries to find a mythological treaure in the sea after tricking Lola into helping them go after it.

episodes.name: Harraslin' Match
episodes.overview: Winslow's Niece and Nephew come to visit and make Winslow look foolish.

episodes.name: Dog the Not So Mighty
episodes.overview: After saving Mayor Rancid the year before, Cat does not want to be Dog's sidekick anymore, but later wants to.

episodes.name: Mean Bob, We Hardly Knew Ye
episodes.overview: CatDog goes to see Mean Bob's Theater play, but Dog thinks it's so real that he starts a fight on stage, this causes Mean Bob (well, the actor that plays Mean Bob) to lose his memory. Dog brings Mean Bob to his house, in order to restore his memory, but since Dog believes that he's the real Bob.

episodes.name: CatDog in Winslowland
episodes.overview: Ever wondered what goes on inside Winslow's house and how he's able to pop out of doorways in so many different locations? Well, so has Cat, and his curiosity finally gets the better of him. He trespasses inside Winslow's hole-in-the-wall.

episodes.name: Cat Gone Bad
episodes.overview: Cat suffers an identity crisis when a gang of beatnik alley-cats set up shop near the CatDog house. Seduced by their bongo music, he trades in his normal, prissy, finicky self to become the cool, hep "Scat Cat". His new alter-ego is much more laid back than the old Cat. In fact, he's so cool with everything he does that he refuses to clean the house, or even pay the bills. It's up to Dog to get the old Cat back that he once knew.

episodes.name: Old CatDog and the Sea
episodes.overview: This is a salty old fisherman's tale about the Swordfish on CatDog's living-room wall. The teller of the tale is Cat, who's embellishing the story in order to impress TV star Tallulah. But Dog can't resist getting in on the act, and spins a wild yarn that Tallulah finds more interesting than Cat's. Cat, frustrated and outdone, finally reveals that the fish was actually purchased at a yard sale.

episodes.name: Cone Dog
episodes.overview: Dog gets an ear injury, forcing him to wear an ear cone.

episodes.name: The Ballad Of Ol' 159
episodes.overview: Pete The Polecat sings about a garbage truck and how Dog trys to save it.

episodes.name: Vexed Of Kin
episodes.overview: Cat believes their parents love Dog more.

episodes.name: Meat Dog's Friends
episodes.overview: Dog finds out meat comes from animals, and his friends are animals!
